definition.value: Any fatty aldehyde that is saturated at positions 2 and 3.
A fatty aldehyde with a trans-double bond at carbon 2.
An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of mitomycin A. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A phenothiazine deriative in which the phenothiazine tricycle has a 3-(dimethylaminopropyl) group at the N-10 position.
An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of mitomycin B. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of 7-demethylmitomycin B.
An organic anion obtained by removal of the acidic proton from position 8 of 7-demethylmitomycin A.

An RNA fragment comprised of six guanosine, seven adenosine, seven uridine and seven cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-A-U-A-U-A-C-A-C-G-C-A-U-A-U-C-A-G-C-G-U-U-C-G-C-G-U.

An RNA fragment comprised of four guanosine, eleven adenosine, two uridine and five cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-G-G-C-A-A-U-A-A-A-A-C-A-C-G-A-C-C-W-U-A-A-U-G.

An RNA fragment comprised of five guanosine, eight adenosine, seven uridine and five cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-U-G-C-G-A-U-U-U-U-A-A-A-G-A-C-C-U-A-G-A-G-U-A-C.

The small nuclear RNA (snRNA) that is a component of U1 snRNP (small nuclear ribonucleoprotein), an RNA-protein complex that combines with other snRNPs, unmodified pre-mRNA, and various other proteins to assemble a spliceosome, a large RNA-protein molecular complex upon which splicing of pre-mRNA occurs.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide obtained by oxygenation of the nitrogen at position 1 on the purine fragment of 3',5'-cyclic AMP.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a dimethylamino group.
An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate composed from twelve isoprenyl units.
An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate composed from thirteen isoprenyl units.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-[(3aS,4S,5R,7aS)-5-hydroxy-7a-methyl-1-oxo-octahydroinden-4-yl]propanoic acid.
An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of all-trans-dodecaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of all-trans-tridecaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylamino group
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is carrying a butyryl substituent.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is carrying a 6-aminohexyl substituent.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cAMP in which the nitrogen atom at position 7 on the purine fragment is replaced by a methine (C-H) group.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cAMP in which the methine (C-H) group at position 8 on the purine fragment is replaced by nitrogen.
A  tertiary amine that is a substituted phenothiazine in which the ring nitrogen at position 10 is attached to C-3 of an N,N-dimethylpropan-2-amine moiety.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is cAMP in which the aza methine (C-H) group at positions 7 and 8 on the purine fragment are transposed.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is 7-deaza-cAMP substituted at position 8 by a chloro group.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 4-chlorophenylthio group.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylamino group.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the hydrogen at position 2 on the purine fragment is replaced by a 6-aminohexylthio group.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having adenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oic acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oic acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxy-9-oxo-9,10-seco-23,24-bisnorchola-1,3,5(10)-trien-22-oic acid.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromoadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
The hydrochloride salt of promethazine.
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Sp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having adenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 8-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphorothioate having 7-bromo-7-deazaadenine as the nucleobase (the Rp-stereoisomer).
A nucleoside 3',5'-cyclic phosphate that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocyclic amino group on the purine fragment is replaced by hydrogen
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP in which the exocylic amino hydrogens on the purine fragment are replaced by methyl groups.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having 2-aminopurine as the nucleobase.
A tricarboxylic acid trianion resulting from the deprotonation of all three carboxy groups of vibrioferrin. The major species at pH 7.3.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having 1-methylguanine as the nucleobase.
An iron coordination entity comprising equimolar amounts of iron(3+) and vibrioferrin(3-).
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as myristoyl (tetradecanoyl).
